<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870422-0009 </DOCNO><HL> Nortek Inc. Agrees to BuyFirm for Over $25 Million</HL><DD> 04/22/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> NTKTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> PROVIDENCE, R.I.  </DATELINE><TEXT>    Nortek Inc. said it agreeddefinitively to purchase closely held Bradford-White Corp.for more than $25 million.   Bradford-White is a Philadelphia-based maker of gas and electric heaters and water purification systems. The company had sales of almost $100 million in 1986, according to Nortek, which makes products for the building, aerospace, industrial and electrical markets.    Ralph R. Papitto, Nortek's chairman, said that Bradford-White would operate as a unit under its present management, with Michael R. DeLuca continuing as chairman and chief executive officer. </TEXT></DOC>